  abstract={This work presents astromorphic transformers, a bio-inspired neural architecture that leverages principles from astronomical observation patterns and cognitive processing mechanisms. We introduce novel attention mechanisms that mimic stellar formation dynamics and gravitational interactions to improve long-range dependency modeling in transformers. The proposed approach demonstrates significant improvements in computational efficiency and representational capacity across multiple cognitive and developmental tasks. Experimental results show enhanced performance in sequence modeling, pattern recognition, and adaptive learning scenarios, with reduced computational overhead compared to traditional transformer architectures. The astromorphic design principles offer new insights into scalable neural network architectures for cognitive developmental systems.},
